title: College football: Aussie punter Blake O’Neill 80-yard kick, fumble, video
text:
Video Image Aussie punter's hero to zero game 1:05 NFL: Michigan punter Blake O?Neill has had a roller-coaster game; he produced the longest punt of the season so far with this 80-yarder, but then he cost his side the game.
October 18th 2015 3 days ago /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/More Sports/ Blake O'Neill punts the ball during the first quarter.
Liam FitzGibbon FOX SPORTS AUSSIE punter Blake O’Neill has experienced the highs and lows of sport in an unbelievable college football match in Michigan.
The former Aussie rules player set tongues wagging with a phenomenal 80-yard punt early in the Michigan Wolverines’ clash with fierce rivals the Michigan State Spartans.
But he was also the man on everyone’s lips for all the wrong reasons after the game.
Michigan punter Blake O'Neill fumbles a punt in the closing seconds. Source: AP
With the Wolverines just 10 seconds away from what look an inevitable victory, Melbourne-born O’Neill botched a last-minute punt to hand the game to the Spartans 27-23.
O’Neill fumbled the snap, lost the ball as he tried to punt it again and the Spartans pounced for a touchdown to complete one of the craziest endings ever seen in college football.
Unsurprisingly, O’Neill copped some nasty treatment on social media after the nationally-televised match but many leapt to his defence.
Hate tweets sent to Blake O'Neill are a disgrace. Ignore them Blake! @blakewoneill True M fans know you are a star. Mistakes happen. @GoBlue
— Gene Sperling (@genebsperling) October 18, 2015 Let's keep it real UM fans. If I'm Blake O'Neill's dad, I'm tempted to wrap him in my arms and never let go. We all bleed red. #MSUvsMICH
— Chris Edwards (@edwardswxwxyz) October 18, 2015 I'm still sick to my stomach for that punter...Blake O'Neill wasn't trying to fail...hoping people have a bit of compassion for him
— Joel Klatt (@joelklatt) October 17, 2015 Many were earlier hailing O’Neill’s booming punt as one of the greatest in college football.
Wow. That's the best punt I've ever seen. Blake O'Neill catches the jet stream for an 80-yarder.
— Dan Murphy (@DanMurphyESPN) October 17, 2015 Lot's of "WOWs" up here in the box on Blake O'Neill's 80-yd punt.
— Ricky Lindsay (@RLindz35) October 17, 2015 Blake O'Neill deserves a lot of credit. Solid punter who continues to pin opponents deep in their own territory. #GoBlue
— Scott C. (@Kilo1899) October 10, 2015 The O'Neill punt is a mainland U-M record, though. Monte Robbins' 82-yarder came in Hawaii.
— Mark Snyder (@Mark__Snyder) October 17, 2015 .
 Aussie punter goes from hero to zero
